I. How we collect and use your personal information
Because WidgetBox does not provide interactive services for information content and does not have an account registration function, WidgetBox does not collect any information about you other than what is necessary to achieve its function.
1. Access to the Software
When you open, and access the WidgetBox App, we will identify your device identity information, i.e., device ID, to confirm your identity for use in the WidgetBox.
2. Create account and use widget services
(1) When You enter texts, pictures, and other contents, we will collect the information you entered for review to ensure that there is no prohibited content in it.
(2) When you add images to widgets, we will request camera, photo, and storage access rights. If you refuse to authorize them, you will not be able to use this feature, but it will not affect your normal use of other features of the WidgetBox.
(3) When using location-related widgets, we request precise geolocation permissions and collect location information related to the services to help you display location when creating or using for location-related service display. If you refuse to provide it, you will not be able to use the location feature, but it will not affect your normal use of other features of the WidgetBox.
(4) When using widgets related to device information, to ensure the normal provision of corresponding functions and the safety of the operating environment, we will collect
the following relevant information:
– (a) Client hardware characteristic information: device model, device hardware serial number, operating system version, battery, signal, and data information.
– Software characteristics information: software version number, browser type.
– Service log information: information you view while using our services, service failure information and other service log information of the same type.
– Other logs and device information:
In addition to the above information, other logs, and device-related information we may collect mainly include: IMEI, MAC, SIM card IMSI identifier, device settings, process and software list, unique device identifier.
3. Other related information
To help you better use our products or services, we may also collect information other than the information listed above:
(1) We may collect information that has been anonymized for research, statistical analysis, and prediction (including using anonymized data for machine learning, training of model algorithms, etc.) for the purpose of improving our products and making commercial decisions.
(2) When you contact us, to verify your identity, we may record your conversations with us and collect other information necessary to resolve the issue.
In any event, we will collect the above information on a “minimal” and “necessary” basis and will protect the data in accordance with the regulations.
4. Exceptions to consent
Please be fully aware that we do not need to obtain your authorized consent for the collection and use of personal information in the following cases (again):
(1) Related to national security, national defense security.
(2) Related to public safety, public health, and significant public interest.
(3) Related to crime investigation, prosecution, trial, and execution of judgments, etc.
(4) For the purpose of safeguarding the life, property and other significant legitimate rights and interests of the subject of personal information or other individuals but where it is difficult to obtain the consent of the individual.
(5) The personal information collected is disclosed to the public by the subject of the personal information himself/herself.
(6) Where your personal information is collected from legitimate public disclosure, such as legitimate news reports, government information disclosure and other channels.
(7) Necessary for the conclusion and performance of a contract at your request.
(8) Those necessary for maintaining the safe and stable operation of the services provided, including the discovery and disposal of service failures or similar situations.
(9) Other circumstances stipulated by laws and regulations.
II. Use and management of COOKIES and similar technologies
(i) Cookies
Cookies are a neutral technology that allows the web server to store data on the client or read data from the client. Cookies are files that store some information related to the user’s visit to the website. Cookie content is usually encrypted, and secure Cookie technology will provide more convenient services for users when surfing the Internet.
(ii) Use of Cookies
The browsing tools you use to open our website may place secure Cookies and related technologies on your computer or mobile device to collect information about you, with the goal of providing you with a more personalized user experience and service. Cookies usually contain identifiers, site names, and some numbers and characters.
You can manage Cookies through your browser settings, including whether to enable and optionally disable them.
However, if you disable Cookies, you may not be able to use certain services. For more information on how to change your browser settings, please visit the relevant settings page of the browser you are using.
III. How We Share, Transfer, and Publicly Disclose Your Personal Information
We will only share, transfer, and publicly disclose personal information when is necessary for the purposes stated in this Policy, and in connection with such sharing, transfer and public disclosure.
(A) Use and provision of personal information
The WidgetBox Operator will not share your personal information with any company, organization, or individual outside of itself without your consent, except in the following cases:
1. Sharing with express authorized consent:
Authorization or consent has been obtained from you or your guardian. If provided at your request to handle disputes or controversies between you and others or in accordance with the relevant agreements signed with you (including the “Software License and Service Agreement for Widgets Box”) or other legal documents.
2. Sharing under statutory circumstances:
Disclosure is required in accordance with relevant laws and regulations, for the needs of litigation activities, or to meet the requirements of judicial or administrative authorities based on statutory procedures. For example, provided to the extent permitted by laws and regulations, and necessary to protect the interests, property, and safety of the WidgetBox, the WidgetBox’s partners, you, other WidgetBox users, or the public from harm.
3. Sharing with affiliates of the WidgetBox Operator:
The WidgetBox Operator may share your personal information with its affiliates in order to provide services to you, to recommend information that may be of interest to you, or to protect you or the WidgetBox Operator’s affiliates or other users from harm to their personal and property safety.
4. Sharing with authorized partners of the WidgetBox Operator:
We may entrust authorized partners to provide certain services to you or perform certain functions on our behalf. To protect the security of your personal information, we will sign appropriate personal information use or confidentiality agreements with our partners before sharing your personal information with them, requiring them to handle personal information in accordance with our instructions, this policy, and any other relevant confidentiality and security measures.
Currently, our authorized partners include the following types:
(1) Authorized partners in the advertising and analytics services category. We do not share your personally identifiable information with partners who provide advertising and analytics services unless we have your permission or unless the data is de-identified and anonymized in accordance with the regulations. We may provide these partners with information about the coverage and effectiveness of their planning reports, but not your personally identifiable information, or we may aggregate this information in anonymized form to ensure that it does not identify you personally. Such partners may combine the above information with other data that they have lawful access to for advertising or decision-making recommendations.
(2) Vendors, Service Providers and Other Partners. Based on business needs, we may send information to vendors, service providers and other partners that support our business by providing technical infrastructure services, analyzing how our services are used, measuring the effectiveness of advertisements and services, providing customer service, facilitating payments, or conducting academic research and surveys. Particularly, when storage services are involved, we will maintain strict confidentiality regarding the content of the storage services performed in accordance with the regulations, and where third-party storage space rental is involved, we will strictly require that such third parties have minimal access to the data and maintain strict confidentiality.
