(B) Transfer
We will not transfer your personal information to any company, organization, or individual, except for the following cases:
1. In the case of obtaining your express consent.
2. In the event of a merger, acquisition or bankruptcy and liquidation involving the transfer of personal information, we will require the new company or organization holding your personal information to continue to be bound by this Policy, or we will require that company or organization to seek your authorized consent again.
3. Provided in accordance with the relevant agreements signed with you (including electronic agreements signed online) or other legal documents agreed to.
4. Provided in accordance with applicable laws and regulations, the requirements of legal proceedings, and mandatory administrative or judicial requirements as may be necessary.
(C) Public Disclosure
We will disclose your personal information publicly only under the following circumstances:
1. With your express consent or based on your active choice.
2. Based on disclosure required by law or regulation: we may disclose your personal information when compelled to do so by law, legal process, litigation or governmental authority.
(D) Sharing, transfer and public disclosure without prior authorized consent
Based on the relevant laws and regulations, prior authorized consent is not required for the sharing, transfer, or public disclosure of your personal information in the following cases:
1. Related to national security or national defense security.
2. Related to public safety, public health, and significant public interests.
3. Related to crime investigation, prosecution, trial, and execution of judgments, etc.
4. To safeguard your or other individuals’ life, property and other significant legitimate rights and interests but for which it is difficult to obtain your consent.
5. Personal information that you disclose to the public on your own.
6. personal information collected from lawful public disclosures, such as lawful news reports, government information disclosure and other channels.
According to laws and regulations, the sharing or transfer of personal information that has been de-identified and ensures that the recipient of the data cannot recover and re-identify the subject of the personal information is not an act of sharing, transferring or publicly disclosing personal information to the public, and the preservation and processing of such data will not require separate notification to you and your consent.
IV. How we protect and preserve your personal information
(i) Protection of personal information
1. The WidgetBox Operator will conduct a rating and security assessment of the WidgetBox in accordance with relevant regulations.
2. We will take reasonable and feasible measures to avoid collecting irrelevant personal information. We will store the personal information collected and generated in the People’s Republic of China in the People’s Republic of China.
3. There are strict data protection and management measures within the WidgetBox Operator, and we will take security measures to strive to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, disclosure, modification, damage or loss and other forms of unlawful processing.
4. In the unfortunate event that the security of the data obtained and stored by the WidgetBox Operator is jeopardized, or the user’s non-public information is disclosed to an unrelated third party due to external actions (e.g. hacker attacks), the WidgetBox Operator will activate the emergency response plan, form an emergency response team, start the process, conduct internal investigation, report and notify the regulatory authorities, and cooperate with the regulatory authorities to reduce the impact of the accident on users, and at the same time will take the form of push notifications, emails, announcements, etc. to inform relevant users.
5. If our products or services are discontinued, we will stop collecting your personal information and inform you of the discontinuation through push notifications and announcements. In any case, we will delete or anonymize your personal information held by us after the termination of service or operation.
(ii) Storage of personal information
The WidgetBox Operator will take appropriate security measures and technical means to store and protect your personal information from loss, misuse, unauthorized access or disclosure, falsification or destruction. We will only store personal information for as long as necessary to achieve the purposes of this Privacy Policy and in accordance with the storage periods corresponding to the different levels of personal information, which are strictly in accordance with the law and relevant regulations. In accordance with the provisions of this clause, we only allow access to personal information to third parties such as employees who have a need to know such information and require them to fulfill the corresponding confidentiality obligations.
V. How you can access and control your personal information
1. Change or withdraw authorization
You can set and modify the device permissions allowed to be accessed by the WidgetBox client through the device’s own permission settings. After the relevant settings and modifications take effect, the WidgetBox Operator will not be able to provide corresponding services to you. Your withdrawal or change of your authorization will not affect the collection and use of personal information previously conducted based on your authorization.
(1)
Turn off notifications: If you do not want to receive notifications from the WidgetBox, you can turn off the “notifications” function through system settings on your device.
(2)
Photo album access: If you do not want the WidgetBox to access your photo album, you can turn off the “photo album” access through the system setting in your device.
(3)
Location access: If you want to turn off the location access, you can do so in your device through the system settings.
2. Account cancellation
The WidgetBox does not provide information publishing service, and there is no account registration function, so you will not have the trouble of not being able to cancel your account.
3. Stop using services
– Except for the notification and photo album functions and the location function, other information collected by WidgetBox is necessary for the basic functions of WidgetBox to work. If you stop using our services, we will delete or anonymize the information collected for the purpose of providing services to you; for information that needs to be retained for a certain period under special circumstances due to laws and regulations, we will not use it again in our daily business activities and take reasonable and appropriate measures to protect it.
VI. How we handle personal information of minors
Minors should obtain the consent of their guardians to use our products or services. If you are a minor under the age of eighteen, you should ask your parent or guardian to read this Privacy Policy carefully before using our products or services and use our products or services or provide us with information with the consent of your parent or guardian. The WidgetBox Operator has the right to recover from your guardian if it holds you liable in accordance with the law or this agreement. If you are the parent or guardian of a minor, you should read all this Agreement in detail before agreeing to give your guardian access to our products or services.
Tip: If you are a parent or guardian of a minor, you should read this Privacy Policy in detail before agreeing to give your guardian access to our products or services, and if you have any questions, you can contact us through the contact information posted in this Privacy Policy.
If you use the WidgetBox, we will assume by default that you have received the foregoing consent. We will protect the personal information of minors in accordance with relevant national laws and regulations and the provisions of this Privacy Policy.
VII. How your personal information is transferred globally
The WidgetBox Operator will store personal information collected and generated during operation in the People’s Republic of China within the territory of China, except in the following cases:
1. Where explicitly provided for by the law of use.
2. Where express authorization has been obtained from you.
3. Where your personal initiative is carried out through the Internet.
For the above cases, the WidgetBox Operator will ensure that your personal information is adequately protected in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
VIII. How this Policy is updated
Considering changes in product form, revisions to laws and regulations, and other factors, we may revise this Policy from time to time, and we will post any changes made to this Policy on this page.
If you disagree with the revised Privacy Policy, you should promptly stop using our related services. If you agree to the newly revised Policy or continue to use our services, it means that you have fully read, understood, and agreed to our Policy.
IX. How to contact us
If you have any questions, comments, or suggestions about this Privacy Policy, you can send the relevant content to: xiaozhihe2021@gmail.com
After we receive your questions, we will process your feedback and respond to you in a timely manner after verifying your identity.
If you are not satisfied with our response, especially if you believe that our handling of personal information has harmed your legitimate rights and interests, you may also seek a solution by filing a lawsuit with a court with jurisdiction in Yangpu District, Shanghai.